# /<active_controller>/grasp_command — issue a one-shot Force-PI grasp command
# to the active demo controller.
#
# Force-PI grasp is a one-shot transition (start grasp / release), not a runtime
# tunable. It cannot live as a ROS 2 parameter (parameters represent state, not
# events). This service is the dedicated channel.
#
# Single-active model: the BT calls the service on the namespace of the
# currently-active controller (e.g. /demo_task_controller/grasp_command). The
# active controller validates and applies; non-active controllers do not
# advertise the server.
#
# E-STOP behavior: while the global E-STOP is active, every command returns
# ok=false with message="E-STOP active".

# Command code:
#   NONE    — no-op (rejected with ok=false; callers should not send NONE)
#   GRASP   — start Force-PI grasp toward target_force
#   RELEASE — release grip (target_force ignored)
uint8 command
uint8 NONE=0
uint8 GRASP=1
uint8 RELEASE=2

# Target grip force [N]. Used only when command==GRASP. Must be > 0.
float64 target_force

---

# True iff the command was accepted and applied to the controller's grasp FSM.
bool ok

# Human-readable summary. On success: "grasp started @ 2.0 N" /
# "release accepted". On failure: explanation (E-STOP, controller not
# grasp-capable, invalid target_force, ...).
string message
